# Pitfalls

Project-specific knowledge base. Each entry is a distilled learning from
resolved issues, grouped by code area. This grows over time as you fix bugs
and discover gotchas.

---

## Authentication

- **Always hash passwords AFTER decoding URL encoding.** The login endpoint
  was URL-encoding passwords before hashing, causing mismatches when passwords
  contained `&` or `=` (I-001). Hash the raw input, encode only for transport.

## Dashboard / Charts

- **Debounce resize observers on chart containers.** Without debounce, charts
  re-render on every resize event causing visible flicker (I-002). Use 150ms
  debounce as minimum.

## General

- **Check all locale-dependent formatting.** Date and number formatting that
  works in en-US may break in other locales. Use InvariantCulture for data
  processing, locale-specific only for display.
